From c1d5bf1f12b9c44a3d12601ab2fac94dd4fcc3a8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: youyx <youxiao@huawei.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 15:00:20 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] [Store] Encapsulate session range transfers in Client
 batch methods
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SubmitRangeRead/Write leaked TransferFuture through the Client API, which
is still exposing transfer internals—just one level above transfer_submitter_.
Match the existing Client::BatchGet style instead: Client owns the whole
transfer (submit-all + await-all) and returns per-entry final results.

- Client::BatchTransferReadRanges / BatchTransferWriteRanges (public): take
  cached replicas + per-entry slices/offsets, submit every fragment in
  parallel and await all, return per-entry bytes-or-ErrorCode. Write variant
  fans out to every memory replica (replication) and counts logical bytes
  once. TransferFuture stays internal to Client.
- SubmitRangeRead/Write demoted to private helpers (used by the sync
  TransferReadRange/WriteRange and the new batch methods).
- RealClient::batch_get/put_into_multi_buffer_ranges now only own session
  state (lease check, overflow check, replica lookup, result merge) and
  delegate the parallel transfer to the Client batch methods. No
  TransferFuture / transfer_submitter_ / master_client_ references remain in
  RealClient.

Session + transfer/put/get/range UTs pass (19 tests).
